HEADWORD: Ulula
<hw>Ul"u*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[L., a
screech owl.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of owls including
the great gray owl (<spn>Ulula cinerea</spn>) of Arctic America, and
other similar species. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Owl</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

